<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Introduction to HTML - Tagveda</title>

    <meta name="description" content="Learn what HTML is, its history and basics with examples on Tagveda.">
</head>
<body>
 <!-- Introduction to HTML Section -->
            <section class="section active" id="introduction">
                <h2 class="section-title">Introduction to HTML</h2>
                <div class="section-content">
                    <h3>What is HTML?</h3>
                    <p>HTML stands for HyperText Markup Language.</p>
                    <p>It is used to create the structure of web pages.</p>
                    <p>HTML tells the browser:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>What is a heading</li>
                        <li>What is a paragraph</li>
                        <li>What is an image</li>
                        <li>What is a link</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p><strong>👉 HTML is NOT a programming language.</strong></p>
                    <p>It is a markup language.</p>

                    <h3>History of HTML</h3>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Invented by Tim Berners-Lee</li>
                        <li>First version released in 1991</li>
                        <li>Current version: HTML5</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h3>Why HTML is used?</h3>
                    <ul>
                        <li>To create websites</li>
                        <li>To structure content</li>
                        <li>To connect CSS and JavaScript</li>
                        <li>Works on all browsers</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h3>HTML vs CSS vs JavaScript</h3>
                    <div class="table-container">
                        <table>
                            <tr>
                                <th>Language</th>
                                <th>Work</th>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td>HTML</td>
                                <td>Structure</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td>CSS</td>
                                <td>Design</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td>JavaScript</td>
                                <td>Functionality</td>
                            </tr>
                        </table>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="quiz-container">
                    <h3 class="quiz-title">Introduction to HTML Quiz</h3>
                    <form id="intro-quiz">
                        <div class="quiz-question">
                            <h4>1. What does HTML stand for?</h4>
                            <div class="quiz-options">
                                <label><input type="radio" name="q1" value="a"> HyperText Markup Language</label>
                                <label><input type="radio" name="q1" value="b"> High Tech Modern Language</label>
                                <label><input type="radio" name="q1" value="c"> Home Tool Markup Language</label>
                                <label><input type="radio" name="q1" value="d"> Hyperlinks and Text Markup Language</label>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="quiz-question">
                            <h4>2. Who invented HTML?</h4>
                            <div class="quiz-options">
                                <label><input type="radio" name="q2" value="a"> Bill Gates</label>
                                <label><input type="radio" name="q2" value="b"> Tim Berners-Lee</label>
                                <label><input type="radio" name="q2" value="c"> Steve Jobs</label>
                                <label><input type="radio" name="q2" value="d"> Mark Zuckerberg</label>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="quiz-question">
                            <h4>3. What is the current version of HTML?</h4>
                            <div class="quiz-options">
                                <label><input type="radio" name="q3" value="a"> HTML4</label>
                                <label><input type="radio" name="q3" value="b"> XHTML</label>
                                <label><input type="radio" name="q3" value="c"> HTML5</label>
                                <label><input type="radio" name="q3" value="d"> HTML6</label>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="quiz-question">
                            <h4>4. Which of the following is NOT true about HTML?</h4>
                            <div class="quiz-options">
                                <label><input type="radio" name="q4" value="a"> It is a markup language</label>
                                <label><input type="radio" name="q4" value="b"> It is a programming language</label>
                                <label><input type="radio" name="q4" value="c"> It creates the structure of web pages</label>
                                <label><input type="radio" name="q4" value="d"> It works on all browsers</label>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="quiz-question">
                            <h4>5. What is the role of CSS in web development?</h4>
                            <div class="quiz-options">
                                <label><input type="radio" name="q5" value="a"> Structure</label>
                                <label><input type="radio" name="q5" value="b"> Design</label>
                                <label><input type="radio" name="q5" value="c"> Functionality</label>
                                <label><input type="radio" name="q5" value="d"> Database management</label>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <button type="button" class="quiz-submit" id="intro-quiz-submit">Submit Quiz</button>
                    </form>
                    <div class="quiz-result" id="intro-quiz-result"></div>
                </div>
            </section>
</body>
</html>

